Macromedia Prepares ColdFusion Upgrade	Macromedia is currently alpha testing an upgrade to its <a href="http://www.betanews.com/article/1061867613" target="_blank">ColdFusion MX 6.1</a> product code-named "Blackstone." Based upon consumer feedback, Macromedia focused on improving three areas: data entry, printing and reporting. A public beta of Blackstone will be available this fall with a final release on tap for early 2005. ColdFusion MX is a product family designed to develop and deploy Web applications and services.
